        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 22 at 3:40PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 340 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 9 miles northwest of San Acacia to 9
miles southeast of Magdalena, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Socorro, Lemitar, Escondida, San Acacia, La Joya, San Antonio,
Chamizal, Luis Lopez and Laborcita.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 380 between Mile Markers 1 and 3.
Highway 60 between Mile Markers 118 and 138.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 139 and 169.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
